Wednesday, September 30, 2009 at 11:04AM

by Kay B. Day



Branded media and blogs are talking about the powers of the federal government in relation to the states, a topic The US Report has covered for months. Fans of Big Government who are equally fond of labels, call those who believe in state sovereignty ‘tenthers.’ To apply labels of our own, we observe neoliberals writing in various statist publications who, perhaps wishfully, call the sovereignty movement
